## Development Environment

### Prerequisites
- macOS with Xcode 15+
- Apple Developer account (free tier works, 7-day certs)
- iPhone 7+ for testing (Simulator won't work)
- iPad for multi-device testing (optional but recommended)

### Setup
```bash
cd ~/projects/mybrick
git clone https://github.com/awaseem/foqos.git
cd foqos
open foqos.xcodeproj
```

### Build & Deploy
```bash
# In Xcode:
# 1. Connect iPhone via USB
# 2. Product → Run (Cmd+R)
# 3. Trust developer on iPhone
```

---

## Project Goals

### MVP (Minimum Viable Product)
- ✅ Scan Brick → iPhone blocks apps immediately
- ✅ iPad syncs and blocks within 30 seconds
- ✅ Scan again → both devices unblock
- ✅ Emergency unbrick via passcode

### Full Product
- ✅ Girlfriend's devices work independently
- ✅ Configurable blocklists (different apps per person)
- ✅ Offline mode (local blocking when no iCloud)
- ✅ Polished UX (haptics, status indicators)

### Non-Goals (Out of Scope)
- ❌ macOS support (too complex, unreliable)
- ❌ Real-time sync (iCloud has inherent latency)
- ❌ App Store distribution (requires $99/year, not needed)
- ❌ Shared blocklists between users (each person independent)

---

## Technical Debt to Avoid

### Don't Build These
- Custom sync protocol (use iCloud KV, don't reinvent)
- Complex user management (Apple IDs handle this)
- Custom NFC protocol (use standard NDEF text)
- Analytics/tracking (privacy-first, local-only)

### Keep It Minimal
- Total new code: ~150 lines
- Reuse Foqos base: ~90% of functionality
- No external dependencies beyond Apple frameworks
- No backend services (everything local + iCloud)

---

## Success Metrics

**Reliability**:
- 95%+ success rate for iPhone blocking
- 85%+ sync success iPhone → iPad
- 100% offline blocking reliability

**User Experience**:
- < 1 second from NFC scan to block
- < 30 seconds for iPad to sync
- < 5 seconds for emergency unbrick

**Maintainability**:
- < 200 lines of custom code
- No external dependencies
- Clear separation of concerns (SyncManager, NFC, UI)

